        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>For the continuum observations, we employ the largest bandwidths available in the ALMA correlator setting in the FDM mode. We cannot use the TDM mode in which total bandwidth is the same as our setting but with lower spectral resolution. As mentioned above, there are lot of molecular lines in Orion KL known as the line forest. By using the most extended configuration, we hope to resolve out most of these line emissions from our continuum data. However, there may be unresolved line emissions which are possibly strong compact emissions such as masers, high excitation transitions, and/or very abundant species. To avoid such contamination efficiently, we employ the FDM mode with the velocity resolution of 0.625 km/s to resolve the line profiles.
</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We employ a single pointing mode with the most extended configuration with the maximum baseline length of 2 km. Field of view in this mode is sufficient to cover the whole of our target source because it will be a compact continuum emission closely associated with a central YSO. The source size is estimated to be 0.2"*0.1" based on previous VLA 43 GHz observations and CARMA 229 GHz observation (Reid et al. 2007, Goddi et al. 2011, Plambeck et al. 2013). To resolve the structure both in major and minor axes, we definitely need highest resolution at 0.04". 
On the other hand, we do not need to recover extended emission component. It is well known that the Orion KL region show number of molecular lines (line forest). These spectral lines could significantly contribute to the continuum emission data unless they are removed in data analysis. In order to avoid such contamination, we try to resolve out as many extended line emissions as possible to employ the longer baselines. Thus, the most extended configuration is the ideal setting for our compact source.
</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
    </prj:ScienceGoal>
